# ============================================
# NOTES FOR TEAM
# ============================================
#
# How to use this file:
# 1. Replace all @username placeholders with actual GitHub usernames
# 2. When creating a Pull Request, GitHub will automatically assign reviewers
# 3. PRs cannot be merged until code owners approve
# 4. To override, you need admin permissions
#
# Best Practices:
# - Keep this file updated when adding new modules
# - Use specific patterns for better control
# - Document why certain files need specific owners
# - Review this file quarterly to ensure it's still accurate
#
# Common Patterns:
# - /path/to/file.js          → Specific file
# - /path/to/folder/          → All files in folder (recursive)
# - /path/to/folder/*         → All files in folder (non-recursive)
# - *.js                      → All JS files in repo
# - /path/**/*.js             → All JS files in path and subfolders
# - /path/file-*.js           → Files matching pattern
#
